Mr. Smith is a 70 year old African American male with PMH of OSA, HTN, COPD/Asthma, HLD, and BPH who presents to MS ED with near syncope and shortness of breath that occurred this morning with associated wheezing and nonproductive cough. He says he was heading out to his car on his motorized wheelchair and when he got up and off the chair, he "blacked out" and fell back into his chair and became increasing short of breath. He felt his heart racing and some blurry vision. He usually uses 3L of home oxygen, but increased it to 3.5L. He denies hitting his head. He denies any chest pain, headache, fevers, chills, nausea, vomiting, or abdominal pain. He says he has also been diagnosed with OSA and has been sent a CPAP at home but has been unable to use it since it was the wrong one. He has been vaccinated for COVID19 x 3. [2]
Pt was admitted, started on therapy for his copd. Pt improved. Pt was found to have diastolic heart failure and started on lasix. Pt found to have a 5 mm nodule on his ct scan and will need a follow up ct scan in 3 months.
